Box.test(ts_store12631, type='Ljung-Box')

Null Hypothesis: indendetly distributed data p-value very small => rejection of null hypothesis and therefore assume dependence

tseries::adf.test(ts_store12631)

Null Hypothesis: non-stationary p-value smaller than printed p-value => reject the null hypothesis =>no trend-stationary

kpss.test(ts_store12631)
#Box-Pierce to check whether data is autocorrelated
Box.test(ts_store12631, type='Box-Pierce')

Null Hypothesis: zero autocorrelation p-value very small => reject the null hypothesis => autocorrelation

#Philips-Perron Test to check order/existence of autocorrelation
tseries:::pp.test(ts_store12631)

Null Hypothesis: non-stationary p-value smaller than printed p-value => reject the null hypothesis => stationary

Null Hypothesis: indendetly distributed data p-value very small => rejection of null hypothesis and therefore assume dependence

# Argumented Dickey Fuller Test to check whether log and first difference data is stationary

Null Hypothesis: non-stationary p-value smaller than printed p-value => reject the null hypothesis =>trend-stationary

#KPSS test for level of stationarity for log and first difference data
kpss.test(ts_store12631_log_D1)
#Box-Pierce to check whether log and first difference data is autocorrelated
